On top of the traditional earth and stone dry-stone bank grows a dense layer of shrubs and trees. These form quite a high barrier. The most usual bushes are{hawthorn}and{hazel.
To keep the hedges tidy and strong they are{trimmed}once a year. They are mostly cut with a tractor mounted flail-mower. These smash up the trimmings into tiny pieces so that they do not need to be collected and burned.
The hedgerow provides a{home and food for all sorts of plants and creatures. When we studied a small section of hedgerow we found over fifty different kinds of{insects.} These attract lots of{birds}and{mammals}
